## 🔴 Pillar 2 — Strict Isolation & Lifecycle Control

| # | OWASP Requirement | Your Project | Status | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 2.1 | Users, sessions, and execution contexts are fully isolated | JWT `sub`/`audience` per agent; rate limits per route | ✅ Compliant | Session identity tied to JWT claims |
| 2.2 | No shared state for user data | Controller is stateless; RWMutex for snapshot reads | ✅ Compliant | No global user state |
| 2.3 | Sessions have deterministic cleanup and enforced resource quotas | Rate limits configured (200/min RO, 60/min RW); resource limits in deployments | ❌ Gap | No explicit session lifecycle management (TTL-based flush of handles, tokens, in-memory context). Relies on token expiry only. No Per-Session Resource Quotas in MCPGovernancePolicy. |
